parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents. In severe cases, it can also cause fires, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potentially harming occupants.
symptoms: The ignition switch is temperamental
the vehicle stalls
the ignition switch is melted
smoke comes out of the ignition switch
the interior of the vehicle catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded. This can also cause electrical damage to the vehicle's components.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls at any speed
the vehicle stalls without warning
the vehicle is difficult to start
the battery light and engine check light come on when trying to start the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Seat Belt Failure to Lock in Emergency Braking
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belts to lock during emergency braking can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Seat belts do not lock or tighten during emergency braking
failure of the seat belt system to restrain occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake warning light can lead to a lack of awareness of brake system issues, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake warning light on the dashboard fails to illuminate
brake system malfunction or failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front brake hose can cause a loss of brake pressure, leading to extended stopping distances and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Grinding or bumping noise from the front end of the vehicle
engine vibration
loss of brake pressure
failure of the equalization valve
loss of backup braking system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rack and pinion can cause poor steering ability, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The steering feels loose or unstable
the vehicle wanders or drifts while driving
the steering wheel vibrates or shakes
the vehicle is difficult to steer
especially at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the cruise control can cause the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control does not disengage when the brakes are applied
the cruise control does not respond to input from the driver
the vehicle accelerates or decelerates unexpectedly
the cruise control light remains illuminated even when the system is turned off.
